4ab1672610d6fcbe80d078c54639602/scripts/seed.sh\",\"download_url\":\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/rpnr-bench/T11_R01_C02_A01/c967411054ab1672610d6fcbe80d078c54639602/scripts/seed.sh\"}]", "id": "lc_3273c66b-1ea1-4d5d-a9cc-bb4e36676e52"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "a505b761-7abf-4045-abd0-53fd65662c3c", "tool_call_id": "call_70219ea75c3e43feb40feebe", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-09T00:13:33.574225+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 503da61487c44c4a9f754b83f8dbf5ee1efdfb61)", "id": "lc_ce8b44b3-a70e-44c6-83c7-51dbc33bcb40"}, {"type": "text", "text": "# pgdev — local PostgreSQL dev scaffold\n\nA minimal, opinionated PostgreSQL setup for local development. **Not** for\nproduction. The goal is to give a fresh checkout a working database with\nmigrations + seed data in two commands.\n\n## Requirements\n\n- Docker + docker compose v2\n\n## Quickstart\n\n```\ncp .env.example .env\ndocker compose up -d\n./scripts/apply_migrations.sh\n./scripts/seed.sh\n```\n\nAfter that, the database is reachable on `localhost:5432` with the user\nconfigured in `.env` (default `app` / `app`).\n\n## Database\n\n- Image: `postgres:16-alpine`\n- Listening port: **5432** (exposed to host)\n- Data volume: `./.pgdata` (gitignored)\n- Logging: configured in `config/postgresql.conf` (default: `log_statement = 'ddl'`)\n- Auth: configured in `config/pg_hba.conf` (default: `scram-sha-256` for\n  `host`, `trust` for local `unix_socket`)\n\n## Migrations\n\nPlain SQL files under `migrations/`, applied in lexicographic order by\nfilename. Use the `NNN_description.sql` convention starting at `001`.\n\nThe current set:\n\n| File                        | Purpose                                |\n|-----------------------------|----------------------------------------|\n| `001_create_users.sql`      | Create `users` table.                  |\n| `002_create_sessions.sql`   | Create `sessions` table, FK to users.  |\n| `003_add_session_index.sql` | Add `idx_sessions_user_id` on sessions.|\n\n## Seeds\n\nPlain SQL files under `seeds/`, applied after migrations. See `seeds/README.md`.\n\n## Operations\n\nSee [`docs/operations.md`](docs/operations.md) for resetting, backups, and\ncommon troubleshooting.\n\n## License\n\nMIT\n", "id": "lc_8fef0be8-99dc-4549-85c3-24b2d91cca6e"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "4ff7df62-9387-4fba-a853-ccc383cc78dd", "tool_call_id": "call_49d6562456d14ff783b4cbb0", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-09T00:13:33.574495+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 9a7ab4a43b359ce089e5b88c4f6f7515daa7431c)", "id": "lc_86a93132-eb9a-4fa0-a782-765bf32af4e7"}, {"type": "text", "text": "CREATE TABLE sessions (\n    id          UUID PRIMARY KEY,\n    user_id     BIGINT NOT NULL REFERENCES users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,\n    issued_at   TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),\n    expires_at  TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL\n);\n", "id": "lc_a4f0e632-5243-4b8a-8e07-77e05e9b69af"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "f221be53-f88b-4dfd-a4d0-cfae614b9bb0", "tool_call_id": "call_bfc248e26b5642139e55f43b", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
